-- Aquarius, AWB, Crown, Nufarm, Foster's, Perseus: Australian, N.Z. Stocks
-- Shani Raja
-- 2010-07-20T06:29:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/aquarius-awb-crown-nufarm-foster-s-perseus-australian-n-z-stocks.html

          
          
             Australia’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index 
advanced 1 percent to 4,403.60 at the 4:10 p.m. close in Sydney.
New Zealand’s  NZX 50 Index  gained 1 percent to 2,995.37 at the 5
p.m. close in Wellington.  
 The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  
 Mining shares: Copper climbed for a second day in Asia.
Copper for three-month delivery on the London Metal Exchange
rose as much as 1.2 percent to $6,588 a metric ton, and traded
at $6,581.50 at 12:02 p.m. in Singapore.  
 BHP Billiton  (BHP AU), the world’s largest mining company,
advanced 1.5 percent to A$38.30.  Rio Tinto Group  (RIO AU), the
world’s third-largest mining company, climbed 2.3 percent to
A$66.50.  
    Aquarius Platinum Ltd.  (AQP AU) increased 14 percent to
A$4.51 after the South African government said a mine safety
order wasn’t intended to stop mining. The fourth-largest
producer of the metal separately said a meeting with the South
African Department of Mineral Resources about the safety
directive was positive and constructive.  
 AWB Ltd.  (AWB AU) rose 1.5 percent to 99 Australian cents.
Australian wheat sales will benefit from adverse weather
conditions affecting Russia, Kazakhstan, Canada and Europe, AWB
General Manager Commodities  Mitch Morison  said in a statement.  
 Crown Ltd.  (CWN AU) gained 3.7 percent to A$7.96.
Australia’s biggest casino owner was raised to “outperform”
from “neutral” at Credit Suisse Group AG.  
 Foster’s Group Ltd.  (FGL AU) rose 2.4 percent to A$5.94.
Australia’s largest brewer has drawn interest from at least two
investment banks conducting due diligence on behalf of clients,
which may make a potential takeover bid for the company’s beer
unit, the Age newspaper reported, without saying where it got
the information.  
      Nufarm Ltd.  (NUF AU) surged 5.2 percent to A$3.42.
Australia’s largest supplier of farm chemicals had its stock
rating raised to “hold” from “sell” by analysts led by
 Belinda Moore  at Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc.  
      Perseus Mining Ltd.  (PRU AU) climbed 5.5 percent to A$2.29.
The mineral exploration company had its stock rating raised to
“buy” from “hold” by analysts led by  Sam Berridge  at Royal
Bank of Scotland Group Plc.  
